1
00:00:08,600 --> 00:00:10,961
♪Love's little quiz
takes seven parts sweet♪

2
00:00:10,962 --> 00:00:13,559
♪And three parts bitter,
till you and I meet♪

3
00:00:13,560 --> 00:00:17,159
♪I pretend I'm not there,
but secretly stay♪

4
00:00:17,160 --> 00:00:26,399
♪Waiting for you♪

5
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:31,400
♪We've got so many
romantic dreams to unfold♪

6
00:00:31,480 --> 00:00:36,224
♪Finally hearing
the I love you I long to hold♪

7
00:00:36,225 --> 00:00:39,839
♪Falling fast
into the swirl of your eyes♪

8
00:00:39,840 --> 00:00:42,399
♪It's just too tempting, so tempting♪

9
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:45,499
♪Never could I have guessed♪

10
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:46,499
♪My heart's rhythm♪

11
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:49,632
♪How beautiful it is, meeting you♪

12
00:01:02,975 --> 00:01:05,961
=Late to Love=
(Adapted from "My Husband Is A Billionaire!")

13
00:01:05,962 --> 00:01:09,107
=Episode 19=

14
00:01:15,499 --> 00:01:17,860
Where do you think
we can hide that's both safe

15
00:01:17,979 --> 00:01:20,099
and lets you keep
working on your experiment?

16
00:01:26,820 --> 00:01:27,780
Beiyan.

17
00:01:31,339 --> 00:01:32,340
Beiyan, Nange.

18
00:01:32,859 --> 00:01:33,978
I heard

19
00:01:33,979 --> 00:01:36,939
Nange's experimental data was stolen,
and they haven't found out who did it.

20
00:01:36,940 --> 00:01:38,659
I happen to have a college classmate

21
00:01:38,660 --> 00:01:40,099
working at a top data security company

22
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:41,739
in Silicon Valley.

23
00:01:41,740 --> 00:01:42,218
This is

24
00:01:42,219 --> 00:01:43,778
their latest tracking software.

25
00:01:43,779 --> 00:01:45,780
I don't know if it'll help.

26
00:01:46,219 --> 00:01:47,700
Who told you that?

27
00:01:49,300 --> 00:01:51,299
Uncle Beixiang accidentally mentioned it

28
00:01:51,339 --> 00:01:52,900
at dinner today.

29
00:01:54,219 --> 00:01:55,220
I...

30
00:01:55,699 --> 00:01:57,379
I'm not overstepping, am I?

31
00:02:01,380 --> 00:02:03,138
Zichen, here's the thing.

32
00:02:03,139 --> 00:02:04,618
Right now, the company's

33
00:02:04,619 --> 00:02:05,498
tech department is

34
00:02:05,499 --> 00:02:07,860
investigating
through our internal system.

35
00:02:08,779 --> 00:02:10,938
If we bring in outside software now,

36
00:02:10,939 --> 00:02:12,460
it could interfere with the process.

37
00:02:14,020 --> 00:02:15,300
I see.

38
00:02:16,900 --> 00:02:17,979
Makes sense.

39
00:02:18,460 --> 00:02:21,139
The company's team
is pretty professional after all.

40
00:02:21,180 --> 00:02:22,620
I was just worried.

41
00:02:22,620 --> 00:02:24,338
As soon as I heard
something happened to Nange,

42
00:02:24,339 --> 00:02:26,099
I wanted to come help.

43
00:02:27,099 --> 00:02:28,340
Thanks for your concern.

44
00:02:28,580 --> 00:02:29,500
Well...

45
00:02:29,580 --> 00:02:30,419
You guys carry on.

46
00:02:30,420 --> 00:02:32,060
If there's nothing else, I'll get going.

47
00:02:38,140 --> 00:02:39,379
Well...

48
00:02:39,420 --> 00:02:40,378
What Zichen said

49
00:02:40,379 --> 00:02:42,180
did remind me of something.

50
00:02:43,140 --> 00:02:44,778
The lab's firewall

51
00:02:44,779 --> 00:02:46,699
really is too weak.

52
00:02:49,499 --> 00:02:51,859
The whole lab isn't very secure.

53
00:02:56,379 --> 00:02:58,139
But don't worry too much.

54
00:02:58,700 --> 00:03:00,979
Danger often comes with opportunity.

55
00:03:01,379 --> 00:03:02,459
Your research may

56
00:03:02,460 --> 00:03:05,419
bring some losses to Huo Group and me.

57
00:03:05,420 --> 00:03:06,939
But this could also

58
00:03:07,180 --> 00:03:07,979
be our chance

59
00:03:07,980 --> 00:03:10,139
to take over Ye Group.

60
00:03:11,379 --> 00:03:13,220
Take over Ye Group?

61
00:03:14,499 --> 00:03:15,618
For the past few years,

62
00:03:15,619 --> 00:03:18,019
Ye Group has
been thriving overseas because of NIT-33

63
00:03:18,020 --> 00:03:19,500
and crushing their competitors.

64
00:03:20,300 --> 00:03:21,579
If we can prove

65
00:03:21,580 --> 00:03:22,579
NIT-33 is

66
00:03:22,580 --> 00:03:23,979
a massive scam,

67
00:03:24,420 --> 00:03:26,659
they will collapse overnight.

68
00:03:26,779 --> 00:03:29,218
When that happens,
Huo Group can buy them out cheap

69
00:03:29,219 --> 00:03:29,938
and complete

70
00:03:29,939 --> 00:03:32,060
a major part
of our pharmaceutical expansion.

71
00:03:36,659 --> 00:03:37,460
Mr. Huo,

72
00:03:38,180 --> 00:03:39,740
you're pretty ambitious.

73
00:03:39,939 --> 00:03:40,979
Of course.

74
00:03:41,140 --> 00:03:43,580
A soldier who doesn't
want to be a general isn't a good soldier.

75
00:03:46,020 --> 00:03:47,338
But isn't

76
00:03:47,339 --> 00:03:49,900
Ye Xin your childhood friend?

77
00:03:49,939 --> 00:03:51,699
Aren't you worried about hurting her?

78
00:03:53,379 --> 00:03:54,938
What kind of question is that?

79
00:03:54,939 --> 00:03:57,019
I've disliked her since we were kids.

80
00:03:57,020 --> 00:03:59,538
The way the Ye family
throws their weight around

81
00:03:59,539 --> 00:04:00,740
has always annoyed me.

82
00:04:00,939 --> 00:04:02,179
Now that we have a chance

83
00:04:02,180 --> 00:04:03,780
to get rid of them,

84
00:04:04,180 --> 00:04:05,500
why wouldn't I take it?

85
00:04:07,059 --> 00:04:09,300
So you've never liked Ye Xin?

86
00:04:09,580 --> 00:04:10,900
Of course not.

87
00:04:18,099 --> 00:04:19,179
Are you jealous?

88
00:04:20,140 --> 00:04:20,978
No.

89
00:04:20,979 --> 00:04:22,220
I'm not jealous.

90
00:04:22,460 --> 00:04:24,940
Not even a little.

91
00:04:25,260 --> 00:04:26,218
You

92
00:04:26,219 --> 00:04:27,260
sure?

93
00:04:29,659 --> 00:04:30,700
Alright.

94
00:04:32,020 --> 00:04:32,778
So where

95
00:04:32,779 --> 00:04:34,460
exactly should we hide?

96
00:04:41,260 --> 00:04:42,780
I thought of the perfect place.

97
00:04:47,580 --> 00:04:50,220
You're hiding me here?

98
00:04:51,620 --> 00:04:52,259
Relax.

99
00:04:52,260 --> 00:04:53,340
It's all set.

100
00:04:53,659 --> 00:04:54,700
Let's take a look.

101
00:04:57,419 --> 00:04:58,299
Let's go.

102
00:04:59,179 --> 00:05:00,780
Careful. Don't bump into anything.

103
00:05:00,900 --> 00:05:02,418
Okay, slow down.

104
00:05:02,419 --> 00:05:03,299
Put it here.

105
00:05:05,299 --> 00:05:06,538
Here.

106
00:05:06,539 --> 00:05:07,459
Alright.

107
00:05:07,460 --> 00:05:08,978
Be careful.

108
00:05:08,979 --> 00:05:09,579
Here.

109
00:05:09,580 --> 00:05:10,539
Leave it here for now.

110
00:05:11,099 --> 00:05:12,858
My room's way too small.

111
00:05:12,859 --> 00:05:13,778
There's no way all

112
00:05:13,779 --> 00:05:15,340
this equipment will fit in here.

113
00:05:15,580 --> 00:05:17,820
Who said there's only one room?

114
00:05:17,940 --> 00:05:18,778
Here.

115
00:05:18,779 --> 00:05:19,700
Take this.

116
00:05:21,099 --> 00:05:22,978
I rented the entire building.

117
00:05:22,979 --> 00:05:23,579
From now on,

118
00:05:23,580 --> 00:05:25,539
this is your lab base.

119
00:05:27,219 --> 00:05:28,200
Then let's do it this way.

120
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:31,059
The first floor will
be the sample storage area.

121
00:05:31,060 --> 00:05:32,820
The ventilation and drainage are great.

122
00:05:32,859 --> 00:05:35,819
The second floor will
be the core lab area.

123
00:05:35,820 --> 00:05:37,178
Quiet and free from distractions.

124
00:05:37,179 --> 00:05:40,059
The third floor will
be for data storage.

125
00:05:40,140 --> 00:05:41,739
Mostly because the lighting's good.

126
00:05:41,900 --> 00:05:43,940
Alright. As long as you like it.

127
00:05:44,060 --> 00:05:45,639
If you need anything else, just tell me.

128
00:05:49,500 --> 00:05:50,499
Thank you.

129
00:05:58,099 --> 00:05:59,220
Not enough.

130
00:06:04,460 --> 00:06:05,139
Mr. Huo,

131
00:06:05,140 --> 00:06:06,099
Mrs. Huo.

132
00:06:17,700 --> 00:06:18,218
Well...

133
00:06:18,219 --> 00:06:19,778
If there's nothing else,

134
00:06:19,779 --> 00:06:20,298
I...

135
00:06:20,299 --> 00:06:21,780
I'll head out first?

136
00:06:21,900 --> 00:06:22,459
Get out.

137
00:06:22,460 --> 00:06:23,539
Go.

138
00:06:24,299 --> 00:06:25,460
You two carry on.

139
00:06:33,099 --> 00:06:34,579
So you've hidden me here.

140
00:06:34,580 --> 00:06:35,819
What about you?

141
00:06:35,820 --> 00:06:37,538
There are a lot
of people outside watching you.

142
00:06:37,539 --> 00:06:39,298
The board, the Ye family.

143
00:06:39,299 --> 00:06:41,260
They're all waiting for an opportunity.

144
00:06:42,580 --> 00:06:44,098
You focus

145
00:06:44,099 --> 00:06:45,940
on the bigger issues.

146
00:06:46,419 --> 00:06:47,460
As for me,

147
00:06:47,659 --> 00:06:49,260
I'll deal with what I

148
00:06:49,339 --> 00:06:50,659
need to handle.

149
00:06:52,339 --> 00:06:53,260
Alright.

150
00:06:53,380 --> 00:06:54,619
Then starting today,

151
00:06:54,620 --> 00:06:56,859
I'm in research mode.

152
00:06:57,900 --> 00:06:59,380
I won't let you down.

153
00:06:59,900 --> 00:07:00,659
Good.

154
00:07:07,739 --> 00:07:09,179
What do you mean you can't find her?

155
00:07:09,339 --> 00:07:11,539
A living person doesn't just disappear!

156
00:07:11,620 --> 00:07:13,939
Mr. Zichen, we've searched
Linhai Medical University,

157
00:07:13,940 --> 00:07:15,978
the Xu family home,
and everywhere Ms. Xu

158
00:07:15,979 --> 00:07:17,858
usually goes, but we found nothing.

159
00:07:17,859 --> 00:07:19,858
According to Shen Yan's people,

160
00:07:19,859 --> 00:07:21,739
Mr. Beiyan arranged for her to return

161
00:07:21,859 --> 00:07:24,059
to her hometown to visit relatives.

162
00:07:24,060 --> 00:07:25,260
Visit relatives?

163
00:07:26,779 --> 00:07:28,619
Didn't I give you
her background report already?

164
00:07:28,620 --> 00:07:31,020
Where would she suddenly get
a hometown and relatives from?

165
00:07:31,339 --> 00:07:32,939
Sorry, Mr. Zichen.

166
00:07:32,940 --> 00:07:34,140
This was our failure.

167
00:07:35,460 --> 00:07:38,538
I don't care if you have
to dig three feet underground. Find her.

168
00:07:38,539 --> 00:07:39,539
Yes.

169
00:07:43,339 --> 00:07:44,340
Zichen.

170
00:07:46,299 --> 00:07:47,380
What's wrong with you?

171
00:07:52,299 --> 00:07:53,259
Nothing, Uncle Beixiang.

172
00:07:53,260 --> 00:07:54,979
My people just messed up.

173
00:07:55,979 --> 00:07:56,940
You're

174
00:07:57,700 --> 00:07:59,700
starting to sound
more and more like Beiyan.

175
00:08:00,419 --> 00:08:01,700
Compared to him,

176
00:08:01,979 --> 00:08:02,978
I'm still far behind.

177
00:08:02,979 --> 00:08:04,260
I've still got a lot to learn.

178
00:08:04,739 --> 00:08:06,259
Don't put too much pressure on yourself.

179
00:08:06,260 --> 00:08:07,580
Get some sleep early.

180
00:08:27,419 --> 00:08:29,019
The key issue isn't willpower.

181
00:08:29,020 --> 00:08:30,218
It's the irreversible

182
00:08:30,219 --> 00:08:31,298
synaptic nerve damage caused

183
00:08:31,299 --> 00:08:32,420
by long-term use.

184
00:08:33,020 --> 00:08:33,899
Exactly.

185
00:08:35,100 --> 00:08:37,019
The three rounds of data released

186
00:08:37,020 --> 00:08:38,538
by Ye Group clearly overlook

187
00:08:38,539 --> 00:08:40,899
the long-term cumulative benefits.

188
00:08:43,059 --> 00:08:44,979
We need to rebuild
the model and strengthen

189
00:08:44,980 --> 00:08:46,979
the time-variable analysis.

190
00:08:51,059 --> 00:08:52,739
(In her field,)

191
00:08:53,340 --> 00:08:55,460
(she's completely different）

192
00:08:55,539 --> 00:08:56,739
（from her usual self.)

193
00:08:57,459 --> 00:08:58,940
(No playfulness.)

194
00:08:59,020 --> 00:09:00,779
(No mischief.)

195
00:09:01,299 --> 00:09:03,300
(Just pure focus.)

196
00:09:03,539 --> 00:09:04,940
(Completely locked in.)

197
00:09:05,779 --> 00:09:07,779
(It's like she's a different person.)

198
00:09:08,620 --> 00:09:11,460
(Xu Nange, trust me.)

199
00:09:12,140 --> 00:09:13,139
(I'll clean up)

200
00:09:13,140 --> 00:09:15,220
(everything out there)

201
00:09:15,740 --> 00:09:18,820
(and protect this peace for you.)

202
00:09:28,140 --> 00:09:28,820
Hello.

203
00:09:29,260 --> 00:09:30,139
Okay.

204
00:09:30,500 --> 00:09:31,499
Got it.

205
00:09:31,659 --> 00:09:32,899
Keep them occupied.

206
00:09:32,939 --> 00:09:34,180
I'll be there in half an hour.

207
00:09:39,659 --> 00:09:40,658
What?

208
00:09:40,659 --> 00:09:42,700
Delay the new drug launch?

209
00:09:42,779 --> 00:09:44,538
Do you realize what that means?

210
00:09:44,539 --> 00:09:46,859
If our competitors launch first,

211
00:09:46,860 --> 00:09:48,540
we'll lose the advantage!

212
00:09:48,579 --> 00:09:50,019
NIT is our only moat

213
00:09:50,020 --> 00:09:51,339
right now!

214
00:09:51,340 --> 00:09:52,058
And if you're

215
00:09:52,059 --> 00:09:54,058
delaying it,
there should at least be a reason!

216
00:09:54,059 --> 00:09:55,499
Stopping it out of nowhere

217
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:57,019
is way too reckless!

218
00:09:58,779 --> 00:09:59,899
Directors,

219
00:10:00,140 --> 00:10:01,420
I have my reasons.

220
00:10:01,459 --> 00:10:02,540
Mr. Huo,

221
00:10:02,900 --> 00:10:05,818
don't gamble
with the entire group's interests.

222
00:10:05,819 --> 00:10:08,178
This doesn't just
involve our group anymore.

223
00:10:08,179 --> 00:10:10,220
It affects Ye Group's interests too.

224
00:10:10,419 --> 00:10:11,859
How are you planning

225
00:10:11,860 --> 00:10:13,818
to explain this to the shareholders?

226
00:10:13,819 --> 00:10:15,700
Precisely
because this involves Ye Group.

227
00:10:16,059 --> 00:10:18,099
This isn't a drug
we developed independently.

228
00:10:18,220 --> 00:10:19,139
There are too many

229
00:10:19,140 --> 00:10:20,979
stages we can't fully control.

230
00:10:20,980 --> 00:10:22,580
That's why we need to be cautious.

231
00:10:22,699 --> 00:10:24,460
This is ridiculous!

232
00:10:25,280 --> 00:10:26,698
You're not taking us seriously at all.

233
00:10:26,699 --> 00:10:27,979
Fine.

234
00:10:29,020 --> 00:10:31,420
Since everyone opposes
delaying the launch,

235
00:10:32,299 --> 00:10:33,580
then let's make a bet.

236
00:10:34,340 --> 00:10:36,259
If NIT-33 is completely fine,

237
00:10:36,299 --> 00:10:37,578
I'll personally cover

238
00:10:37,579 --> 00:10:39,458
all of the group's losses.

239
00:10:39,459 --> 00:10:40,499
At the same time,

240
00:10:40,500 --> 00:10:41,899
I'll resign as CEO

241
00:10:41,900 --> 00:10:43,379
of Huo Group and step down

242
00:10:43,380 --> 00:10:44,259
from the board.

243
00:10:44,260 --> 00:10:45,580
That's way too extreme.

244
00:10:45,659 --> 00:10:48,060
I don't know much about business,
but I remember

245
00:10:48,220 --> 00:10:50,820
Grandma always said,
"Better safe than sorry".

246
00:10:50,900 --> 00:10:51,700
Beiyan,

247
00:10:51,779 --> 00:10:53,178
the risk you're taking is huge.

248
00:10:53,179 --> 00:10:54,778
Does this drug really have a problem?

249
00:10:54,779 --> 00:10:56,019
Directors,

250
00:10:56,140 --> 00:10:57,139
he's doing this

251
00:10:57,140 --> 00:10:58,778
for the group's long-term reputation

252
00:10:58,779 --> 00:11:00,739
and for the safety
of doctors and patients.

253
00:11:00,860 --> 00:11:01,899
I think we

254
00:11:01,900 --> 00:11:03,660
should trust his judgment.

255
00:11:05,659 --> 00:11:06,460
How about this?

256
00:11:07,299 --> 00:11:08,139
Two weeks.

257
00:11:08,140 --> 00:11:10,219
If everything's fine in two weeks

258
00:11:10,220 --> 00:11:12,019
and the approval
comes through on schedule,

259
00:11:12,020 --> 00:11:13,458
we'll move forward as planned.

260
00:11:13,459 --> 00:11:14,460
What do you all think?

261
00:11:15,299 --> 00:11:16,340
Fine.

262
00:11:16,699 --> 00:11:17,940
Two weeks.

263
00:11:18,500 --> 00:11:19,700
What does everyone think?

264
00:11:19,819 --> 00:11:20,660
Fine.

265
00:11:20,699 --> 00:11:22,420
- Alright.
- Fine. No problem.

266
00:11:22,579 --> 00:11:23,460
Mr. Huo.

267
00:11:25,140 --> 00:11:26,058
Mr. Huo, this is bad.

268
00:11:26,059 --> 00:11:27,640
There are tons of reporters downstairs.

269
00:11:27,779 --> 00:11:29,460
- Reporters?
- The reporters are here?

270
00:11:30,539 --> 00:11:31,899
Why are reporters here?

271
00:11:38,779 --> 00:11:39,940
He's here.

272
00:11:40,100 --> 00:11:41,818
Mr. Huo!

273
00:11:41,819 --> 00:11:42,640
Please stop pushing.

274
00:11:42,640 --> 00:11:43,778
Mr. Huo, why did you suspend

275
00:11:43,779 --> 00:11:44,739
the new drug launch

276
00:11:44,740 --> 00:11:45,739
with your partner?

277
00:11:45,740 --> 00:11:46,859
Does this indirectly suggest

278
00:11:46,860 --> 00:11:48,058
the drug has fatal risks?

279
00:11:48,059 --> 00:11:49,219
Your decision may

280
00:11:49,220 --> 00:11:50,739
harm investors' interests.

281
00:11:50,740 --> 00:11:53,139
Do you believe you've fulfilled
your duties as CEO of Huo Group?

282
00:11:53,140 --> 00:11:55,538
Are you confident you can successfully
lead Huo Group through its transition?

283
00:11:55,539 --> 00:11:58,538
First of all, out of responsibility
to the product and to consumers,

284
00:11:58,539 --> 00:11:59,859
we believe the drug needs

285
00:11:59,860 --> 00:12:01,219
a stricter review process.

286
00:12:01,220 --> 00:12:04,019
This has always been a core principle
of both Huo Group and our partner.

287
00:12:04,020 --> 00:12:05,339
As CEO of Huo Group,

288
00:12:05,340 --> 00:12:06,458
every decision I make

289
00:12:06,459 --> 00:12:07,899
is based on the interests of consumers

290
00:12:07,900 --> 00:12:09,220
and investors.

291
00:12:09,260 --> 00:12:09,938
And...

292
00:12:09,939 --> 00:12:11,580
As for Huo Group's transition,

293
00:12:11,659 --> 00:12:13,019
thank you for your concern.

294
00:12:13,020 --> 00:12:14,379
Let's wait and see.

295
00:12:14,380 --> 00:12:16,058
I hope everyone avoids speculation.

296
00:12:16,059 --> 00:12:16,859
If I see any

297
00:12:16,860 --> 00:12:18,619
false statements regarding our company,

298
00:12:18,620 --> 00:12:19,499
we reserve the right

299
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:21,099
to pursue legal action.

300
00:12:23,779 --> 00:12:24,899
Mr. Huo!

301
00:12:25,260 --> 00:12:26,259
Calm down!

302
00:12:27,380 --> 00:12:28,420
(Beiyan,)

303
00:12:29,100 --> 00:12:31,300
(your counterattack has already begun.)

304
00:12:32,100 --> 00:12:34,180
("Let's wait and see," huh?)

305
00:12:34,740 --> 00:12:37,259
(Then let's wait and see together.)

306
00:13:01,208 --> 00:13:04,982
♪What destiny brought us to meet♪

307
00:13:04,983 --> 00:13:08,303
♪Two different worlds, a love so sweet♪

308
00:13:08,308 --> 00:13:11,682
♪A wish we made
in a past life, it seems♪

309
00:13:11,683 --> 00:13:14,537
♪Destined to cross time and dream ♪

310
00:13:14,538 --> 00:13:18,378
♪Like a fairytale story told♪

311
00:13:18,458 --> 00:13:21,715
♪A gentle breeze feels so bold♪

312
00:13:21,733 --> 00:13:25,419
♪As your hair brushes past your ear♪

313
00:13:25,420 --> 00:13:27,777
♪I long to kiss your cheek, my dear♪

314
00:13:27,778 --> 00:13:32,017
♪All my longing, all my love for you♪

315
00:13:32,018 --> 00:13:34,578
♪Has never changed, it's forever true♪

316
00:13:35,020 --> 00:13:41,418
♪It's the hand of fate
that we meet again♪

317
00:13:42,220 --> 00:13:46,658
♪Let me hold you once again♪

318
00:13:46,908 --> 00:13:49,828
♪Resting against your chest♪

319
00:13:50,178 --> 00:13:55,419
♪Your warmth shines like stars at night♪

320
00:13:55,420 --> 00:14:00,219
♪Let me kiss you once again♪

321
00:14:00,220 --> 00:14:03,019
♪No reason needed♪

322
00:14:03,020 --> 00:14:05,217
♪My heart belongs to you♪

323
00:14:05,218 --> 00:14:10,938
♪I'm not afraid
to cross time to find you♪

